  <h1> WHAT IS AN AMERICAN TABLE SET-UP?</h1>
          
  
  <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2320/0269/files/ALS_American_Formal_Dining_Table_Setting_v02_A3.png?271" alt="American Table Setup">>
  <h2> An American table setup, often called American service, refers to a dining arrangement where all utensils, plates, and glassware are placed before the meal begins.
    Typically, the plate is centered with the fork on the left and the knife and spoon on the right, with the knife blade facing the plate. A water glass is placed above the knife, while a napkin is either folded to the left of the forks or placed on the plate.
    This setup is more casual compared to European settings, allowing for quicker and more efficient service in many restaurants and homes.</h2>
   
  </section>
