           <h1>UTENSILS AND PROCEDURE</h1>
          
<img src=" https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRSJx-ywnV6qcJs1nNCk_8EZLKrw9MhF5ZfGWeSK2KF6dXbk5g8ZI-fAK1k&s=10">
  <h2>The procedure for an American table setup starts with placing the dinner plate at the center. 
    The fork goes to the left of the plate, while the knife and spoon are placed to the right, with the knife blade facing the plate.
    A water glass is set above the knife, with additional glasses to its right if needed. The napkin is folded and placed either to the left of the fork or on the plate.
    This arrangement is simple and practical, designed for ease of service and comfort.</h2>
